A Meru senator aspirant Kobia Maranya (pictured) has promised to root for the construction of Meru-Mombasa super highway, which will pass through Kitui. He said the road will shorten the distance between Meru and Mombasa. &ldquo;I will lobby for this road. It must be a super highway with eight lanes,four on each side. Mombasa is only 375 kilometres from Meru if the road is built,&rdquo; the independent candidate said, adding it will boost tourism.Maranya spoke at Ruiri market, North Imenti, on Tuesday.